This info applies only to the win32 port, and only when running NT: I
was perplexed by the fact that HexMode was a lot slower than the other
modes. After some fiddling I've come to realize that the speed of the
console output routines in Windows depend greatly on how varied the
colour attributes are. Little variance makes for great speed; great
variance makes for little speed. I therefore recommend that you set the
"Background" colour in HexMode to the same colour as "Hexfield
(normal)". Try it out if you think HexMode is sluggish. Some speedups
can be made in CodeMode and DumpMode as well by altering their
background colours. Note: versions after v1.54 have these colours
configured correctly per default.

